Class DataSelectionSet

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Searchable, Selectable, SelectionSet
public class DataSelectionSet
extends BaseSelectionSet

This class is suitable for small selection sets created from a Cursor, where the calling code needs to retain the Data after using the Cursor. You should avoid using the add(DataID) method and use add(Identifiable) method instead. If you choose to call add(DataID), you must ensure that the DataID is an EmbeddedDataID.

DataSelectionSet

public DataSelectionSet(Selectable selectable)
Constructs a DataSelectionSet for the specified Selectable. If you use the add method to poulate this SelectionSet, then each DataID must be constructed using the EmbeddedDataId class. You can also use the getAllData method later.

Parameters:
selectable - the Selectable
See Also:
EmbeddedDataID, add(java.lang.Comparable)

DataSelectionSet

public DataSelectionSet(Selectable selectable,
                        Cursor cursor)
Constructs a DataSelectionSet for the specified Selectable, and populates it with DataIDs obtained from the Cursor. The Cursor must contain Identifiable Data, otherwise a ClassCastException will be thrown.

The Identifiables will be embedded within the DataIDs. Each DataID will be constructed using the EmbeddedDataID class

Parameters:
selectable - the Selectable
cursor - the original Cursor
See Also:
EmbeddedDataID
